  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "c5613bf0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "9. When using a Gaussian mixture model, can you name two techniques for determining the correct\n",
    "number of clusters?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "340b5af9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "ans:\n",
    "An approach is to find the clusters using soft clustering methods and then see if they are gaussian. If they are then you can apply a GMM model which represents the whole dataset."
   ]
